  "texts": [
    "In parallel, we clustered all genes into 1,090,132 de novo gene families, which accounted for 95% of all plasmid genes (Fig. 1b and Supplementary Fig.",
    "1a) and constituted the primary data for the training of PlasX (Fig. 1, Supplementary Fig.",
    "1b, c and Supplementary Information).",
    "PlasX is a logistic regression that assigns a positive or negative coefficient to gene families that are likely to originate from sequences that are of plasmid or non-plasmid origin (Fig. 1c).",
    "The algorithm predicts whether or not a given sequence is a plasmid by considering the coefficients of all gene families in the sequence, and assigns a score to each prediction that ranges between zero and one; a prediction score of >0.5 suggests that the sequence is more likely to be a plasmid than not."
  ],
